section.para:
Snippets are delimited by /*#inline
    on a line by itself, followed by the target source code, followed by
    */ on a line by itself.  C++ style comments 
    (comments preceeded with "//") are allowed inside 
    a snippet.  Here is an example:

    
    /*#inline
      // Don't Panic
      int a = 42;
      printf( "The answer is %d\n", a ); 
    */

XMI is an acronym for XML Metadata Interchange.  &bp; &escher; 
    supports the ability to export your models in XML format using XMI 2.1.  
    XMI is an Object Management Group (OMG
    ) specification for the use of XML in serializing models so 
    that they can be imported, exported and interchanged.
